# Resource-Driven Retail Intelligence Upgrade

Transform the pipeline from a generic "Computer Vision Project" into a **Retail Intelligence System** by integrating the three hackathon resources as first-class architectural components.

---

## Context

The current system uses generic zone IDs (`ZONE_1`, `ZONE_4`) and lacks real POS ground-truth correlation. The hackathon provides three resources that most candidates will treat as reference files. We'll treat them as **ground truth inputs**:

| Resource | File | Role |
|----------|------|------|
| Store Layout Excel | `Brigade Road - Store layoutc5f5d56.xlsx` | Ground Truth Store Topology |
| POS Transaction CSV | `Brigade_Bangalore_10_April_26 (1)bc6219c.csv` | Ground Truth Purchase Signal |
| Evaluation Framework PDF | `Assessment Evaluation Frameworkb24a398.pdf` | Scoring Checklist |

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Store Layout → Zone Polygons**: The Excel file contains only images (no structured data). We will manually transcribe the brand shelf positions from the layout image into normalized coordinates in `store_config.json`. The zones identified from the **"Revised" layout** (Image 0) are:
>
> **Top wall (left→right):** EB Korean, The Face Shop, Good Vibes, DermDoc, Minimalist, Aqualogica, Lakme Skin, Accessories
>
> **Bottom wall (left→right):** Maybelline, Faces Canada, Lakme, Colorbar+Sugar, Swiss Beauty, Renee/NY Bae, Alps Goodness, Streax
>
> **Center:** F.O.H (Front of House), Nail Unit, Fragrance, Makeup Units
>
> **Right side:** Cash Counter (Billing), PMU (Permanent Makeup Unit)
>
> **Left side:** Entry Door (curved glass door)
>
> The polygons will be defined as normalized [0..1] coordinates relative to frame dimensions, since actual pixel mappings depend on the camera angle and would need calibration per camera. A CLI tool will also be provided to help calibrate these.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **POS CSV Schema Change**: The real POS CSV uses columns `order_id`, `invoice_number`, `order_date`, `order_time`, `store_id` (value: `ST1008`), `store_name` (`Brigade_Bangalore`), `brand_name`, `product_name`, `qty`, `NMV`, `total_amount` etc. The current `POSCorrelator` expects `timestamp` and `store_id` columns. We need to adapt the parser to handle both the real CSV schema and the generic one.

> [!WARNING]
> **Evaluation Scoring Breakdown** (from the PDF):
> - Detection Pipeline: **30 marks** (entry/exit accuracy, re-entry/staff handling, edge cases)
> - API & Business Logic: **35 marks** (endpoint correctness, funnel logic, anomaly detection)
> - Production Readiness: **20 marks** (docker, observability, testing)
> - Engineering Thinking: **15 marks** (CHOICES.md, DESIGN.md, reasoning depth)
>
> **Key insight**: API & Business Logic is the highest-weighted category (35 marks). Brand-level analytics directly strengthens this score.

