### Layer 1 — POS Correlator Upgrade (`src/pos/`)

#### [NEW] [parser.py](file:///c:/Users/BIT/Purplle_Hackathon/src/pos/parser.py)
Parse the real POS CSV with its actual schema:
- Combine `order_date` + `order_time` → UTC datetime
- Map `store_id` (`ST1008`) to pipeline store_id
- Extract: `invoice_number`, `brand_name`, `product_name`, `qty`, `total_amount`, `customer_name`
- Group line items by `order_id`/`invoice_number` into `POSTransaction` objects
- Each transaction = one unique invoice (may have multiple line items/brands)

#### [NEW] [correlator.py](file:///c:/Users/BIT/Purplle_Hackathon/src/pos/correlator.py)
Enhanced POS correlator replacing the existing `pos_correlator.py`:
- Match visitor exit times to POS timestamps within configurable window (±5 min)
- Extract **brands purchased** from matched transaction line items
- Set `session.converted = True`, `session.purchase_amount`, `session.brands_purchased`
- Track which brands were visited vs which were purchased (for shelf conversion)

#### [NEW] [conversion.py](file:///c:/Users/BIT/Purplle_Hackathon/src/pos/conversion.py)
Conversion attribution engine:
- `overall_conversion_rate()` — visitors who purchased / total visitors
- `shelf_conversion(zone_id)` — visitors to zone who later purchased
- `brand_conversion(brand)` — visitors to brand zone who purchased that brand
- `cross_sell_paths()` — common zone visit sequences before purchase

